yourself with a crossbow.

01:19.855 --> 01:22.106
You should try the red velvet. It's new.

01:22.107 --> 01:23.190
Oh, jeez.

01:23.191 --> 01:24.609
Do I look like an idiot to you?

01:24.610 --> 01:26.110
No.

01:26.111 --> 01:28.112
You think you can squeeze
an extra dollar out of me

01:28.113 --> 01:30.782
because it's, like, "Ooh, trendy,
it looks like its bleeding"?

01:30.783 --> 01:32.825
No, in your heart of hearts,
you know as well as I do,

01:32.826 --> 01:34.952
red velvet is bullshit.

01:34.953 --> 01:37.539
It tastes like Play-Doh.
It is not velvety.

01:37.540 --> 01:40.292
And the only thing that's good about
it is the cream cheese frosting

01:40.293 --> 01:42.960
which is meant to live on top of
carrot cake, like God intended.

01:42.961 --> 01:45.963
Okay, panda. We hear you.

01:45.964 --> 01:48.800
Red velvet isn't a thing.

01:48.801 --> 01:50.978
Red velvet can go to hell.

01:53.096 --> 01:56.775
You give me two Long Johns and a jelly.

02:03.941 --> 02:06.859
[sighs] Well, I'll be fucked.

02:06.860 --> 02:08.026
What happened?

02:08.027 --> 02:09.788
Mind your own beeswax, Donuts.

02:13.158 --> 02:14.877
Oh, you kidding me?

02:15.411 --> 02:19.590
If I was a lesser person,
I would say, "I told you so."

02:21.083 --> 02:23.426
[man speaking indistinctly on PA]

02:29.800 --> 02:31.926
All right, here we are.

02:31.927 --> 02:34.971
Welcome to Litchfield, two-point-nothing.

02:34.972 --> 02:37.890
So recently, we did go from,
uh, public to private,

02:37.891 --> 02:39.892
which is quite a relief.

02:39.893 --> 02:44.564
God bless free market America
of the United States.

02:44.565 --> 02:45.690
[inmate] "Free market"?

02:45.691 --> 02:48.693
Yeah, I worked the night shift
at Sam's Club a while back

02:48.694 --> 02:49.986
and they used to lock us in.

02:49.987 --> 02:52.364
Well, it was probably for
your own protection. [scoffs]

02:52.365 --> 02:53.823
Yeah, it didn't feel like that.

02:53.824 --> 02:56.242
Well, look... [scoffs] you kidding me?

02:56.243 --> 03:01.623
The government socialists are clearly so
far up your butt crack about equality,

03:01.624 --> 03:06.469
when, in code, it's all about just
giving the darker people free shit.

03:07.212 --> 03:11.298
It's all about private corporation
because they really look after us.

03:11.299 --> 03:13.050
And you get religious freedom.

03:13.051 --> 03:16.804
- Yeah, I'm not that religious.
- No? Well, that's too bad.

03:16.805 --> 03:19.932
'Cause if you were a Christian, you
could tell everybody what to do,

03:19.933 --> 03:22.059
and then they do it so they
don't hurt your feelings,

03:22.060 --> 03:23.770
because that's against the law.

03:23.771 --> 03:25.104
[snaps fingers] Come on.

03:25.105 --> 03:28.149
Okay, so this right here
is Mr. Healy's office.

03:28.150 --> 03:29.567
He's one of the counselors.

03:29.568 --> 03:32.069
Now, some of the girls, they
like the black one better, okay?

03:32.070 --> 03:33.237
But, listen...

03:33.238 --> 03:36.491
He brings snacks sometimes and
he's kind of a silver fox.

03:36.492 --> 03:39.411
Down here, we've got visitation.
Down here, okay?

03:39.412 --> 03:41.287
Your family is allowed
to come and see you,

03:41.288 --> 03:44.049
but if they never do...

03:44.750 --> 03:48.085
that's probably just
'cause they're too busy.

03:48.086 --> 03:51.297
But they still care about you. For sure.

03:51.298 --> 03:52.924
For sure.

03:52.925 --> 03:55.468
This place is amazing.

03:55.469 --> 03:57.637
All right, this is still
prison and all, right?

03:57.638 --> 03:59.514
There's no need to jump off the deep end.

03:59.515 --> 04:02.642
We got off the van,
like, five minutes ago,

04:02.643 --> 04:04.226
and I haven't heard anybody screaming.

04:04.227 --> 04:05.770
And the walls are so clean.

04:05.771 --> 04:08.398
[Pennsatucky] Yeah, and we
just got new mattresses, too.

04:08.399 --> 04:10.983
Yes. This here is Chang.

04:10.984 --> 04:12.193
Chang!

04:12.194 --> 04:15.488
So, she works in the commissary.
She don't talk much.

04:15.489 --> 04:17.113
Ching Chong Chang!

04:17.115 --> 04:19.366
Fuck you, cracker.

04:19.367 --> 04:21.452
[laughs] She loves when I do that.

04:21.454 --> 04:23.213
[woman speaking indistinctly on PA]

04:26.667 --> 04:28.710
[Alex] How's life in the panty mill?

04:28.711 --> 04:31.838
Uh, yesterday, we learned
everything about sewing,

04:31.839 --> 04:34.549
including how to serge with a rolled hem

04:34.550 --> 04:37.927
and use a zigzag stitch.

04:37.928 --> 04:41.815
I don't really know what any of it
means, so today's gonna be awesome.

04:45.769 --> 04:48.020
What... [laughs]

04:48.021 --> 04:49.522
How's grounds crew treating you?

04:49.523 --> 04:52.066
The instructions are pretty clear.

04:52.067 --> 04:55.319
Dig. Rake. Schlep.

04:55.320 --> 04:56.403
[Piper] Uh-huh.

04:56.404 --> 04:58.573
[Alex scoffs] It's fine.
And it's outside.

04:58.574 --> 05:02.243
Anything is better than being stuck
down in that sweaty basement

05:02.244 --> 05:05.005
with the fucking puppets
from The Dark Crystal.

05:06.206 --> 05:08.165
I'm thirsty just looking at her.

05:08.166 --> 05:10.835
[whispering] Well, you should
see what she does with pepper.

05:10.836 --> 05:12.336
Hey, lesbians.

05:12.337 --> 05:15.140
My eyes squinty, but ears work fine.

05:15.591 --> 05:17.142
Let's go.

05:18.051 --> 05:19.844
I'm sorry.

05:19.845 --> 05:23.774
- I laugh when I see something super weird.
- [hushed] Alex! Alex!

05:24.307 --> 05:27.069
[Alex] How did she get
a whole box of salt?

05:29.522 --> 05:31.438
[woman speaking Mandarin]
He should be here any minute now.

05:31.439 --> 05:32.690
[man] Is he bringing his checkbook?

05:32.691 --> 05:36.736
Between her plane ticket and bus fare
to Beijing, I'm in for almost a grand.

05:36.737 --> 05:39.363
Flight reimbursement
is included in the deal.

05:39.364 --> 05:42.033
What if I don't like him?

05:42.034 --> 05:44.326
Then you can go back to Hebei
Province and grow potatoes.

05:44.327 --> 05:45.963
[knocking on door]

05:48.456 --> 05:50.508
Don't say anything stupid.

06:10.938 --> 06:12.564
Is this a joke?

06:12.565 --> 06:14.941
Welcome to our family, Mr. Sun.

06:14.942 --> 06:16.901
My sister and I are so
pleased to meet you.

06:16.902 --> 06:19.070
You promised me a beautiful girl.

06:19.071 --> 06:21.113
I never actually said "beautiful."

06:21.114 --> 06:23.490
You said she had "pleasing attributes."

06:23.491 --> 06:25.993
And I'm sure she does.

06:25.994 --> 06:28.663
My sister's a good cook.
And very thrifty.

06:28.664 --> 06:30.247
So am I.

06:30.248 --> 06:32.959
And I paid to find a wife,

06:32.960 --> 06:36.003
not a squatty peasant who
still smells like sheep shit.

06:36.004 --> 06:38.806
Call me when you want to get serious.

06:39.633 --> 06:42.060
We had a deal! Son of a bitch.

06:44.179 --> 06:46.013
What do we do now?

06:46.014 --> 06:48.400
I don't want to go back to China.

06:48.934 --> 06:50.685
I can't take care of her.

06:50.686 --> 06:52.519
Do you have any idea how much she eats?

06:52.520 --> 06:55.064
Business has been terrible.

06:55.065 --> 06:58.067
You must know someone
else who needs a wife.

06:58.068 --> 07:02.947
I'm only as good as the product.

07:02.948 --> 07:09.880
If you don't have the looks,
you at least need charm.

07:11.039 --> 07:13.290
How about finding someone less picky?

07:13.291 --> 07:16.669
It's not like this guy
was on the A-list.

07:16.670 --> 07:18.295
[sighs]

07:18.296 --> 07:19.847
What am I going to do?

07:20.883 --> 07:23.685
I could help you in the shop.

07:24.469 --> 07:26.521
You owe me eight hundred dollars.

07:28.056 --> 07:30.767
[indistinct chatter on TV]

07:30.768 --> 07:32.894
[reporter]
That was the scene just a few minutes ago

07:32.895 --> 07:35.396
outside this Lower Manhattan courthouse,

07:35.397 --> 07:37.982
where culinary celebrity Judy King

07:37.983 --> 07:40.567
was arraigned on charges of tax evasion.
According to authorities...

07:40.568 --> 07:43.320
I never liked this woman.

07:43.321 --> 07:47.167
She puts cream in her carbonara.
It's vulgar.

07:49.327 --> 07:50.745
What are you writing?

07:50.746 --> 07:52.789
It's for drama workshop.

07:52.790 --> 07:56.626
It's about my emotionally
manipulative asshat of a mother

07:56.627 --> 07:58.670
and all the times she betrayed me.

07:58.671 --> 08:00.462
I'm thinking at the end,

08:00.463 --> 08:02.757
I could run her over
with a riding lawnmower.

08:02.758 --> 08:04.133
Shred the bitch.

08:04.134 --> 08:05.927
Oh, that's beautiful, honey.

08:05.928 --> 08:10.565
You can watch your cartoons later.
It's the grown-ups' time now, honey.

08:13.101 --> 08:16.103
Hey, Red. I hear you
got family in Queens.

08:16.104 --> 08:17.438
What about them?

08:17.439 --> 08:20.107
I was wondering if your husband could
give my son a ride up here sometime?

08:20.108 --> 08:22.276
I'll trade you whatever.
I've asked everyone, but...

08:22.277 --> 08:24.787
Dmitri won't be visiting anymore.

08:25.488 --> 08:28.416
Oh, shit. I'm sorry.

08:29.242 --> 08:31.828
He's a worthless mushroom of a man.

08:31.829 --> 08:33.245
I've known a few of those.

08:33.246 --> 08:35.414
Maybe we should give up and be gay.

08:35.414 --> 08:36.498
We got the haircuts.

08:36.499 --> 08:38.301
[laughs]

08:46.551 --> 08:49.846
There an angle in this
place you ain't workin'?

08:49.847 --> 08:52.264
Watch and learn, Mendoza.

08:52.265 --> 08:53.349
[clicks tongue]

08:53.350 --> 08:55.110
[Red chuckles]

08:55.936 --> 08:57.644
[exclaims sharply]

08:57.645 --> 09:00.356
The food lady from the TV got arrested!

09:00.357 --> 09:03.317
- Wait, what? Oh, shit, is it Nigella?
- Mmm-mmm.

09:03.318 --> 09:04.819
- The trashy one?
- Mmm-mmm.

09:04.820 --> 09:06.278
- The snotty one?
- Mmm-mmm.

09:06.279 --> 09:09.490
Ooh, it's the one with the plantation
kinda vibe goin' on, but in a fun way?

09:09.491 --> 09:11.283
- Yes!
- [laughs]

09:11.284 --> 09:14.536
- Yes! Had something to do with her taxes.
- [Poussey] Yeah, Judy King!

09:14.537 --> 09:17.749
There was microphones everywhere.
And they almost stuck one in her ear.

09:17.750 --> 09:19.416
Oh, Lord, if you're really out there,

09:19.417 --> 09:21.753
please, please, please
let her come to Litchfield.

09:21.754 --> 09:24.130
Please, please, please.

09:24.131 --> 09:25.473
[Crazy Eyes] Um...

09:26.299 --> 09:27.767
[Poussey] What?

09:29.302 --> 09:32.013
I think your laundry might be alive.

09:32.014 --> 09:35.516
Nah, that's that furry alkie
been stealing my jail juice!

09:35.517 --> 09:37.476
Yeah, I caught it this morning.

09:37.477 --> 09:40.062
I'll turn that punk into a hat. [laughs]

09:40.063 --> 09:41.230
What?

09:41.231 --> 09:44.867
Okay. We gonna have to talk.

09:46.111 --> 09:47.412
What?

09:49.990 --> 09:51.333
[sighs]

09:51.950 --> 09:54.118
So, stations one and two,

09:54.119 --> 09:57.914
you will be at the cutting tables
this morning cutting patterns.

09:57.915 --> 10:00.582
And then everyone else can
start assembling the pieces.

10:00.583 --> 10:03.961
We will switch out after
lunch to avoid fatigue.

10:03.962 --> 10:06.005
[Anita laughs]

10:06.006 --> 10:09.550
Look sharp, ladies. It's up to us to
help the lovers of the world get it on!

10:09.551 --> 10:11.103
[scatting]

10:12.763 --> 10:14.055
That's enough, DeMarco.

10:14.056 --> 10:17.058
Come on, Donaldson. Live a little, huh?

10:17.059 --> 10:18.976
Cut it out, okay?

10:18.977 --> 10:20.978
This shit's right up my alley.

10:20.979 --> 10:24.023
Sewed all my kids' clothes
until high school.

10:24.024 --> 10:26.033
- [chuckles]
- I bet they loved that.

10:28.528 --> 10:32.531
Man, somehow my khakis be
feelin' extra khaki right now.

10:32.532 --> 10:35.868
Oh, come on, Gonzales.
Looks are superficial.

10:35.869 --> 10:41.091
Everybody knows it's about talent,
originality, a sense of humor...

10:42.584 --> 10:45.502
[both snickering]

10:45.503 --> 10:50.091
[snorting] What do you think it's
like to be her in real life?

10:50.092 --> 10:52.927
Mmm, she eats pills and ice
cream, and cries at night.

10:52.928 --> 10:55.897
And she cuts herself, but on
her scalp so no one can see.

10:56.473 --> 10:58.265
So, it's still better than our lives.

10:58.266 --> 11:00.652
I would be her in a second.

11:06.316 --> 11:09.276
[sighs] White bitches, white bitches...
All right, check it.

11:09.277 --> 11:12.404
How many pages you think it is
before they put in a token blackie?

11:12.405 --> 11:16.450
And how dark is she, scale
of one to Grace Jones?

11:16.451 --> 11:19.620
All right, 14 and four.

11:19.621 --> 11:22.581
All right, 14 and four. Let's find out.

11:22.582 --> 11:24.208
[exclaims]

11:24.209 --> 11:27.419
- So close. Here she is, page 11.
- Oh, man!

11:27.420 --> 11:29.171
- Man, but that's not too bad.
- Mmm-hmm.

11:29.172 --> 11:31.558
But she, like, a two.

11:31.716 --> 11:33.717
- The bitch got blue eyes.
- Yeah, true.

11:33.718 --> 11:35.677
But, damn, look at her abs, though.

11:35.678 --> 11:37.013
I know, right?

11:37.014 --> 11:39.306
So I jump out the window.

11:39.307 --> 11:43.810
I fall two floors, I land
on the awning, I slide off.

11:43.811 --> 11:48.900
I grab the delivery boy's bicycle,
and I'm outta there. I'm gone.

11:48.901 --> 11:51.485
And that is how I pull off

11:51.486 --> 11:55.832
the biggest jewel heist
in Chandler, Arizona.

11:56.324 --> 11:59.743
I gotta say, you are the cutest
gunslinger I've ever met.

11:59.744 --> 12:01.870
[giggles] Thank you so much.

12:01.871 --> 12:03.414
And I do love guns.

12:03.415 --> 12:07.293
I mean, the old ones...
and the newer ones.

12:07.294 --> 12:10.046
I'm saving up for a 1962 Remington 700.

12:10.047 --> 12:11.255
That's the year they came out.

12:11.256 --> 12:14.341
Push-feed action,
3.2-millisecond lock time.

12:14.342 --> 12:16.468
Ooh! Just hearing you talk about that

12:16.469 --> 12:18.387
makes me want to go out
and shoot something.

12:18.388 --> 12:21.933
[groans] Now you're making me sad.

12:21.934 --> 12:24.819
You're never gonna be able
to buy a gun again, are you?

12:25.228 --> 12:26.437
What?

12:26.438 --> 12:31.826
As a convicted felon, you can't own a gun.

12:32.235 --> 12:33.620
Oh, right.

12:34.321 --> 12:35.913
Right!

12:36.364 --> 12:38.449
That is terrible, isn't it?

12:38.450 --> 12:41.660
I mean, that should be
a fundamental right.

12:41.661 --> 12:43.870
Like freedom of speech, right?

12:43.871 --> 12:46.457
I mean, what is happening to our country?

12:46.458 --> 12:48.209
It's the fall of Rome.

12:48.210 --> 12:51.721
[scoffs] Don't even get
me started on Rome.

12:53.381 --> 12:56.342
I've never written to an inmate before.
I didn't know what to expect.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.760
But you're... great.

12:58.761 --> 13:01.273
[sighs] You're great, too.

13:01.514 --> 13:02.681
Can I come see you again?

13:02.682 --> 13:05.267
I think that would be fine.

13:05.268 --> 13:07.603
Did you think we weren't gonna find out?

13:07.604 --> 13:11.940
I never found out. Nobody said
a damn word to me about an ad.

13:11.941 --> 13:13.985
All due respect, sir, but
I am gonna have to call

13:13.986 --> 13:16.112
a massive amount of bullshit on that.

13:16.113 --> 13:21.033
My kid's got asthma, and out of pocket,
her inhaler costs like $300 a month.

13:21.034 --> 13:22.618
I could get heroin for cheaper.

13:22.619 --> 13:24.745
- I understand.
- Do you?

13:24.746 --> 13:27.831
'Cause it seems like the only job
you saved around here was your own.

13:27.832 --> 13:30.667
You're still full-time. You
still have health insurance.

13:30.668 --> 13:36.173
You think that's what this is about, huh?
I got mine, now I'm gonna cut you loose?

13:36.174 --> 13:39.218
It doesn't not look like that, does it?

13:39.219 --> 13:42.939
I guess we can put the couch on
Airbnb to pay for your wrist surgery.

13:43.640 --> 13:45.400
Listen to me.

13:46.434 --> 13:49.978
Even if I didn't give two
shits about you clowns,

13:49.979 --> 13:51.897
which is not the case,

13:51.898 --> 13:54.733
I would still want to fix this
just to get you off my jock.

13:54.734 --> 13:56.152
I promise you.

13:56.153 --> 14:00.332
I think that was his way of saying
he cares what happens to us.

14:01.199 --> 14:02.408
Exactly.

14:02.409 --> 14:05.587
If you care about us, you should say it.

14:06.579 --> 14:07.954
Say you care about us.

14:07.955 --> 14:09.256
No.

14:09.874 --> 14:11.500
Say you love us.

14:11.501 --> 14:13.669
What? We're family in here.

14:13.670 --> 14:17.006
You love us and you're gonna
turn this thing around.

14:17.007 --> 14:18.433
Say it.

14:18.841 --> 14:20.393
[mutters indistinctly]

14:22.220 --> 14:23.938
[sighs]

14:25.015 --> 14:26.557
I...

14:26.558 --> 14:27.808
I love you.

14:27.809 --> 14:29.736
[Ford] That's more like it.

14:36.526 --> 14:38.610
[indistinct chatter]

14:38.611 --> 14:41.822
Hi, I would like a kosher meal, please.

14:41.823 --> 14:43.324
We got beef, noodles and peas.

14:43.325 --> 14:45.034
It's a religious thing.

14:45.035 --> 14:49.255
Which means Uncle Sam says you
gotta provide it when asked for.

14:49.622 --> 14:51.332
That's actually true.

14:51.333 --> 14:53.667
Well, we don't have it.

14:53.668 --> 14:55.961
Kosher's in extra deep freeze.

14:55.962 --> 14:59.215
Where it's been for months
because nobody ever asked for it

14:59.216 --> 15:03.094
when they were eating tasty,
nutritious Russian fusion.

15:03.095 --> 15:04.479
But now...

15:05.472 --> 15:07.774
this is what it's come to.

15:18.025 --> 15:20.370
Some tweaker wants kosher.

15:21.279 --> 15:24.990
We don't got enough to deal with
around here, now we got Jews?

15:24.991 --> 15:27.076
La Red says it's in the back.

15:27.077 --> 15:28.670
[chuckles]

15:46.679 --> 15:49.315
This actually looks pretty good.

15:52.102 --> 15:54.529
No noodles. All peas.

15:57.815 --> 16:01.368
- You want cake?
- Just peas. Two milk.

16:35.520 --> 16:38.397
Food is to be eaten in the cafeteria.

16:38.398 --> 16:40.399
Yeah, totally. I'm just
running out real quick.

16:40.400 --> 16:42.193
- I'm gonna come right back.
- Really?

16:42.194 --> 16:44.986
Or are you going to stash that
cake in your locker for later

16:44.987 --> 16:48.240
and then pretend you don't know
why there are roaches in B-Dorm?

16:48.241 --> 16:51.034
My dreams make me hungry.

16:51.035 --> 16:53.087
[sighs]

17:42.379 --> 17:43.930
[Brook groans]

17:44.130 --> 17:46.098
You know what sucks?

17:46.716 --> 17:49.801
Belonging to a race that doesn't
commit enough low-value crimes

17:49.802 --> 17:52.137
to be relevant in a place like this.

17:52.138 --> 17:54.556
Where's my big, Asian prison family?

17:54.557 --> 17:56.475
You Scottish.

17:56.476 --> 17:58.352
[Brook] Not to white people I'm not.

17:58.353 --> 18:00.186
One drop of ethnic blood and bam!

18:00.187 --> 18:03.189
I'm basically made in China,
like you and my toothbrush.

18:03.190 --> 18:04.951
You Scottish.

