36:46.438 --> 36:50.158
Fucking me. I even have a
uniform and everything.

36:52.403 --> 36:54.612
- Let's get through this, Maxwell.
- [sighs]

36:54.613 --> 36:56.697
I'm gonna show them
that I'm a good pawn

36:56.698 --> 36:57.990
and that I'm willing to play ball.

36:57.991 --> 36:59.492
And then in a few months, I tell them,

36:59.493 --> 37:04.214
"Look, we tried it your way.
Now, I need my guys full-time."

37:05.206 --> 37:07.258
I miss Fig.

37:08.919 --> 37:11.262
Right. Right.

37:12.423 --> 37:15.090
Send one of these jokers
back to my office.

37:15.091 --> 37:16.175
Which one?

37:16.176 --> 37:17.811
Thrill me.

37:19.137 --> 37:21.263
[Healy] Hey! Hey, boss man.

37:21.264 --> 37:23.223
I got interviews, Healy.

37:23.224 --> 37:25.861
With those yahoos in the lobby? Yikes.

37:26.352 --> 37:28.438
I don't envy your job today.

37:28.439 --> 37:30.230
I've never felt closer to you.

37:30.231 --> 37:35.486
Hey, listen, I don't know what else
these MCC goons got up their sleeve,

37:35.487 --> 37:38.363
but I want you to know I got
full confidence in you.

37:38.364 --> 37:42.242
I know you're doing the best that you can.
I can see that.

37:42.243 --> 37:43.411
Thank you.

37:43.412 --> 37:45.871
Us old-timers gotta stick together, okay?

37:45.872 --> 37:47.966
I got your back all the way.

37:50.461 --> 37:52.220
I appreciate that.

37:53.213 --> 37:55.214
Good luck, all right?

37:55.215 --> 37:58.852
Oh, hey, uh, do me a favor and
sign this real quick for me.

38:03.640 --> 38:05.641
You want Reznikov back in the kitchen?

38:05.642 --> 38:07.893
She was running a whole
black market outta there.

38:07.894 --> 38:09.144
Yeah, but that wasn't proven.

38:09.145 --> 38:10.771
And we got all new vendors
in the kitchen now.

38:10.772 --> 38:14.525
And don't forget, we just lost
Gonzales to the underwear people.

38:14.526 --> 38:16.193
[sighs] I don't know.
I don't know, Healy.

38:16.194 --> 38:17.277
I'll keep an eye on her.

38:17.278 --> 38:20.531
She'll start off in the bottom,
washing dishes, doing the onions.

38:20.532 --> 38:22.667
We got a lot bigger problems, here, man.

38:24.495 --> 38:25.995
[pen scribbles]

38:25.996 --> 38:28.748
Do not mistake my kindness
for weakness, Counselor.

38:28.749 --> 38:29.915
[pen clacks]

38:29.916 --> 38:32.928
I'll keep that in mind. Side Boob!

38:40.093 --> 38:42.062
[sewing machines whirring]

38:54.190 --> 38:55.491
[Piper] Huh.

38:55.692 --> 38:57.327
Uh, Mr. Brand?

38:58.278 --> 39:03.282
You know, if you smush these patterns
just a little bit closer together,

39:03.283 --> 39:07.703
you can actually get an extra
Lacy Low-Rider Indiscretion bikini

39:07.704 --> 39:09.789
from the same piece of fabric.

39:09.790 --> 39:12.592
Thanks for your advice, inmate.

39:13.251 --> 39:15.178
It was really more of an observation.

39:15.546 --> 39:20.433
Let's just assume that Whispers Inc.
knows how they want to make panties, okay?

39:23.679 --> 39:24.845
[Stella] See?

39:24.846 --> 39:28.817
Even C-minus-looking people can be stupid.
[chuckles]

39:36.567 --> 39:37.900
You closin' up?

39:37.901 --> 39:39.359
I got time for one more.

39:39.360 --> 39:40.996
I need my neck shaved.

39:41.446 --> 39:43.948
No one ever wants
anything fun around here.

39:43.949 --> 39:45.324
I'm guessing fun, to you,

39:45.325 --> 39:48.077
means a 2-foot poufy thing
with a birdcage in it?

39:48.078 --> 39:52.331
And what would be so terrible about that?
I mean, especially in a place like this.

39:52.332 --> 39:55.793
We could use some...
some originality, some sass.

39:55.794 --> 39:58.554
Mmm-mmm. Not getting
noticed is my main goal.

39:59.172 --> 40:02.382
[sighs] Sass is what lands you in Seg.

40:02.383 --> 40:04.134
[Sophia chuckles] I feel that.

40:04.135 --> 40:06.511
[laughing] Really? 'Cause
you doin' the opposite.

40:06.512 --> 40:10.015
You got this whole thing going
on, the hair, the makeup...

40:10.016 --> 40:13.936
I mean, who has the energy to
go full MAC counter every day?

40:13.937 --> 40:19.024
Listen, after all I went through to be
me, I'm not about to let shit slide.

40:19.025 --> 40:22.653
Yeah, but you all up in our face with
it, like all blown out and shit.

40:22.654 --> 40:24.780
Look, if you wanted to
look like a real woman,

40:24.781 --> 40:29.252
you would let your roots grow out
and get some bags under your eyes.

40:30.328 --> 40:33.789
You know, historically,
me and reality...

40:33.790 --> 40:35.332
not friends.

40:35.333 --> 40:37.126
Mmm. You got me there.

40:37.127 --> 40:40.713
This one time, I'm getting on
the Metro-North to head home,

40:40.714 --> 40:42.172
and this mouth-breather,

40:42.173 --> 40:44.216
this mouth-breather
comes right up behind me

40:44.217 --> 40:45.384
and smacks me on the ass.

40:45.385 --> 40:47.720
- And I'm thinking...
- I'm sorry, could you go back a second

40:47.721 --> 40:50.190
to the part where you're
on the Metro-North?

40:50.431 --> 40:51.515
What about it?

40:51.516 --> 40:53.934
- Where you live?
- Yonkers.

40:53.935 --> 40:56.228
Childhood home of
Mary J. Blige and Anthrax.

40:56.229 --> 41:00.107
[chuckles] You know that my son, you
know, Benny, he's in the Bronx.

41:00.108 --> 41:01.233
Mmm-hmm.

41:01.234 --> 41:02.484
Yeah.

41:02.485 --> 41:04.569
You think that maybe, um...

41:04.570 --> 41:07.572
he could ride up here
sometimes with your wife?

41:07.573 --> 41:08.741
You know, for visitation.

41:08.742 --> 41:11.461
'Cause he could take the
bus to their house.

41:13.038 --> 41:14.755
I'll ask her.

41:15.123 --> 41:16.424
[chuckles]

41:17.542 --> 41:19.334
I'm feeling sassier already.

41:19.335 --> 41:21.471
- Mmm-hmm?
- [chuckles]

41:21.922 --> 41:24.849
Glad you could come out for a real visit?

41:25.550 --> 41:27.310
Nice drive.

41:28.428 --> 41:32.607
First time in prison's always weird.
You must feel like a starling.

41:33.433 --> 41:35.184
A what now?

41:35.185 --> 41:37.102
A common starling.

41:37.103 --> 41:39.354
You know, how they weren't
native to America

41:39.355 --> 41:42.107
and then that guy Eugene
brought them over,

41:42.108 --> 41:44.869
'cause he wanted it to be
like Shakespeare's time.

41:46.487 --> 41:48.539
Right, sure.

41:50.491 --> 41:54.078
I think I saw a hermit thrush, yesterday.

41:54.079 --> 41:57.340
At least, I think it was a hermit thrush.
It was all by itself.

41:57.958 --> 41:59.759
My uncle had a parakeet.

42:00.626 --> 42:04.180
Knew how to swear in Italian,
but he shit all over the house.

42:07.759 --> 42:10.645
You're not that into
birds, are you?

42:11.637 --> 42:15.566
Got nothing against them, but mostly
I'm into Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu.

42:16.309 --> 42:17.860
Like I wrote you.

42:18.228 --> 42:22.064
Oh, sure, Jiu-Jitsu.
Everybody loves Jiu-Jitsu.

42:22.065 --> 42:23.699
It's delicious.

42:26.903 --> 42:28.779
You wanna tell me what's going on here?

42:28.780 --> 42:31.866
No, nothing, nothing. Nothing's going on.
It was just a little misunderstanding...

42:31.867 --> 42:33.408
You think I'm some bird guy?

42:33.409 --> 42:35.160
- No.
- What is this? Is this a scam?

42:35.161 --> 42:36.829
Trying to get money or something?

42:36.830 --> 42:38.122
No, no, no, no, no!
It's not about money...

42:38.123 --> 42:39.498
I'm supposed to believe that?

42:39.499 --> 42:42.635
You're the top contract killer
in Jackson Hole, Wyoming.

42:43.628 --> 42:45.462
Look...

42:45.463 --> 42:48.215
the only person that cared about me,

42:48.216 --> 42:51.102
they took her away to Max.

42:52.303 --> 42:54.314
And I'm so lonely.

42:54.514 --> 42:59.059
[voice breaking] And I thought,
if I wrote to enough people,

42:59.060 --> 43:02.572
then maybe I would find
somebody and, oh... [sobbing]

43:03.398 --> 43:06.576
I watched so much Discovery Channel.

43:07.652 --> 43:09.037
[sniffles]

43:11.281 --> 43:12.873
[man sighs]

43:15.994 --> 43:17.503
Hold up, hey.

43:18.413 --> 43:19.797
Hey.

43:22.751 --> 43:25.678
I don't care how many
other guys you wrote.

43:26.296 --> 43:29.057
I'm just glad I get to meet you.

43:30.591 --> 43:32.017
[sighs]

43:33.386 --> 43:38.849
"I'm glad you confronted me about
your feelings, Gina-bo-bina.

43:38.850 --> 43:43.938
I see now that the way I
treated you was wrong."

43:43.939 --> 43:46.031
"Thank you, Mom.

43:46.357 --> 43:50.078
I feel so much better
about our relationship.

43:50.779 --> 43:53.831
If you weren't dead, I'd hug you."

43:54.532 --> 43:58.753
"I think you forgot that
anything is possible...

44:00.121 --> 44:02.507
in your imagination."

44:03.666 --> 44:05.343
You hug. You hug.

44:06.419 --> 44:07.803
Oh.

44:10.173 --> 44:12.341
[Rogers] Very nice, ladies.

44:12.342 --> 44:16.095
And a big hand to Gina who shared
a piece of her life with us.

44:16.096 --> 44:18.013
[scattered applause]

44:18.014 --> 44:20.975
Dead is dead is gone forever.

44:20.976 --> 44:23.518
You don't say that you
can still give hugs.

44:23.519 --> 44:25.280
It's irresponsible.

44:26.189 --> 44:27.272
Because you can't.

44:27.273 --> 44:30.109
You regularly talk to a mop.

44:30.110 --> 44:31.318
[inmate] Burn!

44:31.319 --> 44:32.870
[Rogers] Okay.

44:33.113 --> 44:34.497
Okay.

44:36.491 --> 44:38.209
[Gina whispers] You did great.

44:39.077 --> 44:40.670
Who's next?

44:43.664 --> 44:45.883
Come on...

44:46.459 --> 44:48.719
Anyone?

44:52.173 --> 44:53.683
[man grunting]

45:00.932 --> 45:02.567
Ahh!

45:09.149 --> 45:10.491
Ahh!

45:10.901 --> 45:12.410
[coughing]

45:17.240 --> 45:19.900
[Fu speaking Mandarin] This is
the fuckwad who rejected you?

45:20.076 --> 45:24.004
It's not like I'm looking
at God's gift here.

45:24.747 --> 45:26.299
Right?

45:27.625 --> 45:28.959
I remember you.

45:28.960 --> 45:33.223
What do you want us to do with him?

45:37.468 --> 45:40.179
[imitating Chang]
"Cut out his gall bladder!"

45:40.180 --> 45:43.015
"Please, no! I was dummy.

45:43.016 --> 45:45.309
- I made big mistake.
- [chuckles]

45:45.310 --> 45:49.396
You are strong and
beautiful, like a horse.

45:49.397 --> 45:51.190
Please, forgive me."

45:51.191 --> 45:53.534
[laughing maniacally]

45:54.610 --> 45:56.787
"Too late for sorry, now.

45:57.738 --> 45:59.323
[stutters]

45:59.324 --> 46:01.208
Kill him!"

46:01.492 --> 46:06.839
[Angie] "I must die now for
being the worst person.

46:07.165 --> 46:10.385
I accept your wisdom.

46:11.086 --> 46:12.720
Girl power."

46:15.256 --> 46:17.132
[gurgling]

46:17.133 --> 46:18.934
[imitates blood spurting]

46:20.386 --> 46:22.429
- [laughing]
- [inmates exclaiming]

46:22.430 --> 46:25.724
"And now I eat his... " [sighs]

46:25.725 --> 46:28.727
Okay, I don't feel comfortable saying this.
It's disgusting.

46:28.728 --> 46:30.729
Okay, okay. We can stop here.

46:30.730 --> 46:33.607
I did say to re-imagine old resentments,

46:33.608 --> 46:36.452
but I think you took this a little
too far to be constructive.

46:37.403 --> 46:38.612
I liked it.

46:38.613 --> 46:40.623
[inmates murmuring]

46:49.249 --> 46:50.716
All fake.

46:51.334 --> 46:52.802
Showbiz.

46:53.336 --> 46:55.513
Yeah, see...

47:01.886 --> 47:03.887
Hey, Big Talkin' Missy.

47:03.888 --> 47:05.972
Out of the kitchen, into the sweatshop.

47:05.973 --> 47:07.807
Turns out your mobility
ain't so upwards, huh?

47:07.808 --> 47:09.684
Fuck off, Ruiz.

47:09.685 --> 47:11.728
At least my hair doesn't
smell like a deep fryer.

47:11.729 --> 47:12.979
[chuckles]

47:12.980 --> 47:16.033
Uh-uh. I'm gonna eat one of them
kosher meals y'all got back there.

47:16.859 --> 47:17.984
You ain't even Jewish.

47:17.985 --> 47:20.371
You think you know my life?

47:21.114 --> 47:23.532
- Fine.
- [Black Cindy] Yeah.

47:23.533 --> 47:25.460
Shabbat shalom, bitch.

47:26.411 --> 47:28.787
How much longer you gonna stay mad?

47:28.788 --> 47:32.374
Man, do you know how hard it is to
get a squirrel into a laundry bag?

47:32.375 --> 47:33.917
[laughs] No.

47:33.918 --> 47:36.753
I took it a little too far,
hooch jacking you.

47:36.754 --> 47:40.132
But you was pissin' and settin'
traps like Elmer Fudd.

47:40.133 --> 47:42.810
Man, the shit was funny.
[laughs]

47:45.971 --> 47:48.515
But also, I was worried about you.

47:48.516 --> 47:50.725
Well, you know, if I
was worried about you,

47:50.726 --> 47:53.187
I'd have made you some
goddamn soup or something.

47:53.188 --> 47:54.947
Excellent point.

47:55.565 --> 47:58.108
But you think you might want to
cut down on the sauce, though?

47:58.109 --> 48:00.026
Like, just to make sure you can?

48:00.027 --> 48:02.612
- I ain't hurtin' nobody.
- Um... [taps fork]

48:02.613 --> 48:05.490
Excuse me, Miss Poussey?
This is your liver speakin'...

48:05.491 --> 48:08.293
It just makes me feel better, okay?

48:09.954 --> 48:12.382
It makes me feel like I
can get through this.

48:15.418 --> 48:17.052
Come with me to AA.

48:17.462 --> 48:19.296
- [scoffs]
- Come on, man. It'll be fun.

48:19.297 --> 48:21.465
You ain't even a addict!

48:21.466 --> 48:24.801
You just make up crazy stories about
shit that ain't even happened.

48:24.802 --> 48:25.927
- So?
- And then everybody

48:25.928 --> 48:28.180
gotta listen to you. It's
your personal open mic night.

48:28.181 --> 48:32.392
Well, instead of poetry slam,
it's like poetry slammer.

48:32.393 --> 48:33.518
No.

48:33.519 --> 48:36.521
[imitating Cinque] Come on,
like, "Give us, us freestyle."

48:36.522 --> 48:39.233
Oh, you pullin' out the
Amistad, now. Damn.

48:39.234 --> 48:40.660
[chuckles]

48:41.611 --> 48:42.986
[clears throat]

48:42.987 --> 48:46.331
I just feel like this
place is beatin' me down.

48:48.784 --> 48:51.953
I don't need no audience to talk at.

48:51.954 --> 48:53.338
[chuckles]

48:54.874 --> 48:57.259
I need a girlfriend.

48:59.337 --> 49:01.305
Like, a real one.

49:01.881 --> 49:03.265
You know?

49:06.136 --> 49:07.562
Love.

49:11.474 --> 49:15.894
[woman on PA] MCC is looking to train
you for your job on the outside.

49:15.895 --> 49:18.280
See human resources.

49:27.282 --> 49:28.749
No!

49:30.034 --> 49:31.669
[breathing heavily]

49:33.163 --> 49:35.539
O'Neill, I hired a new guard.

49:35.540 --> 49:37.166
First of many.

49:37.167 --> 49:40.678
And I'm gonna need you guys
to show him the ropes.

49:42.463 --> 49:44.474
Help yourself.

49:48.553 --> 49:50.720
Red velvet is shit.

49:50.721 --> 49:52.607
[toilet flushes]

49:57.102 --> 49:58.937
You like Bo Derek.

49:58.938 --> 50:01.240
Tarzan, 1981.

50:02.942 --> 50:05.995
Please pretend that you
didn't just see this.

50:08.072 --> 50:10.199
I don't see nothing.

50:10.200 --> 50:12.710
I just wanted to feel pretty.

50:21.252 --> 50:22.928
Chang?

50:25.465 --> 50:28.518
I'm... sorry about the other day.

50:30.345 --> 50:32.688
Thank you, lesbian.

50:40.646 --> 50:43.699
[speaking Mandarin] What do
you want us to do with him?

50:50.197 --> 50:54.168
You will always be an ugly
girl who no one wants.

50:54.785 --> 50:57.287
Whether I live

50:57.288 --> 50:59.248
or die,

50:59.249 --> 51:01.551
nothing will change that.

51:04.420 --> 51:06.096
He's right.

51:09.759 --> 51:11.435
Nothing will change.

51:12.928 --> 51:14.220
Mei!

51:14.221 --> 51:15.898
What should we do with him?

51:17.683 --> 51:19.694
Should we let him go?

51:22.688 --> 51:24.323
Nah.

51:25.775 --> 51:27.577
Cut out his gall bladder.

51:29.654 --> 51:30.945
[man yelling] No!

51:30.946 --> 51:33.332
- [knife plunges]
- [man screaming]

